programme.title: Phil Spencer: Secret Agent
programme.desc: The property expert arrives in Scotland to find buyers for two homes suffering from the same problem - absent owners. Patricia Cameron is struggling to sell her 1950s three-bedroom house in Edinburgh, while brothers John and Paul Campbell are encouraged to clean up their bungalow in Largs, North Ayrshire.(n)

programme.title: Phil Spencer: Secret Agent
programme.desc: Phil is in Warrington, where he meets Pauline and Alan Jacks, who have been trying to sell their three-bedroom property. He soon realises potential buyers may have been deterred by the dated decor, cuddly toys, tapestries and dolls dotted around the place. A few miles away, Colin Brunold has been hoping his four-bedroom family home would sell itself, but a dodgy chimney could be putting off house-hunters.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Reg and Aby Solomon from Hertfordshire look to buy a family holiday home near the Spanish town of Denia on the popular Costa Blanca. Laura Hamilton searches every nook and cranny of the local market in an attempt to find properties that match the couple's £200,000 budget, but it remains to be seen whether she can deliver the perfect place in the perfect location.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Husband and wife Tracey and Gareth Sadd from Wales love the northern part of Tenerife and are keen to find a bolt-hole that they can escape to regularly. Presenter Jasmine Harman searches the local market to find properties to match the couple's £110,000 budget in the hope that they'll like one of them enough to make an offer.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Liverpool couple John and Pauline McDonough both have demanding jobs in the pharmaceutical industry and want to find a relaxing bolt-hole to escape to in Spain's Granada province. Laura Hamilton shows them five properties starting at just under £86,000 in the hope that they will make an offer.(n)

programme.title: Ramsay's Hotel Hell
programme.desc: Gordon Ramsay checks in at the 90-year-old Monticello Hotel in Longview, Washington, where owner Phillip Lovingfoss has an apparent liking for alcohol that some of his staff claim is threatening to destroy the business. The challenge of turning around the hotel's fortunes only increases when the chef sees shocking allegations about Phillip splashed all over the front page of the local newspaper.(n)

programme.title: Ramsay's Hotel Hell
programme.desc: In Oregon, Gordon Ramsay tries to rescue the Applegate River Lodge, which is around $1million in debt. The chef questions whether owner Richard Davis's interest in smoking cannabis is distracting him from the problems at this family-built inn, and encounters Richard's sons Duke and Dusty, whose fiery relationship seems to prevent them from working together to tackle the establishment's financial troubles.(n)

programme.title: Ramsay's Hotel Hell
programme.desc: Gordon Ramsay visits Starkville, Mississippi, to try to rescue the failing Hotel Chester. Despite having more than 40 years' experience in the business, owner David Mollendor is at a loss as to how to make his dream of owning his own hotel work, while his wife Sukie is struggling as its chef, tackling the role without any formal catering experience. Gordon discovers a family tragedy that explains why this couple have become trapped in their business and wrestling with debt.(n)

programme.title: Location, Location, Location
programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp and Phil Spencer guide artist Zena Ellis as she takes her first step on to the housing ladder in Luton with a budget of £125,000. Also seeking assistance are new parents Lysan and Bo Cheng, who want to move out of London and return to Bedfordshire for a slower-paced family life, but find £550,000 doesn't go far in their chosen part of the country.(n)

programme.title: Location, Location, Location
programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp tries to find a peaceful North Yorkshire home for Susanna and Phil, an unconventional couple with a complementary health therapy business. Also in the region, Phil Spencer helps Trudie and Steve and their two sons, who are relocating from Edinburgh to be nearer their relatives.(n)

programme.title: Location, Location, Location
programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp and Phil Spencer help two couples house-hunting in north-west London. Tony and Michelle have already looked at almost 100 properties during their search for a £900,000 dream pad with enough space for their large record collection. Meanwhile, Amy and Takbir are desperate to get on the first rung of the ladder, but despite some military-style planning, have had no success in the competitive market.(n)

programme.title: Hunt for the Arctic Ghost Ship
programme.desc: Cameras follow the multi-million-dollar expedition that discovered the Victorian ship HMS Erebus, intact and upright on the Arctic sea floor in September 2014. The story unfolds in the freezing Arctic, where search vessels battled with heavy sea-ice that threatened to stop the search entirely, to the dramatic chain of events that led to the historic discovery.(n)

programme.title: Gogglebox
programme.desc: The nation's favourite armchair critics share their opinions on what they have been watching during the week. The programme captures their instant reactions and lively - sometimes emotional - discussions from the comfort of their own homes.(n)

programme.title: First Dates
programme.desc: Twenty-five-year-old businessman Justin has never had a girlfriend and has turned to self-help manuals to improve his understanding of women so model booker Maisie is in for a big surprise when he uses what he has learnt from the books. After her first date at the restaurant didn't work out, Teresa, 66, hopes to find someone who shares her passion for partying, so she might have found her ideal match when 79-year-old Lee arrives with a hangover.(n)

programme.title: Married at First Sight
programme.desc: A team of experts including psychologist Mark Coulson, relationship and sex therapist Jo Coker, anthropologist Dr Anna Machin and Church of England vicar Nick Devenish set out to help another pair of singletons find 'the one'. Meeting just before they walk down the aisle, the experiment follows the newlywed couple through the first weeks of their relationship to see if people really can fall in love at first sight.(n)

programme.title: Ramsay's Hotel Hell
programme.desc: Gordon Ramsay checks in to Murphy's Historic Hotel near Sacramento in northern California, where owners Brian, Kevin and Joel are often too distracted by their lively bar to look after their business. The national landmark, which has played host to an array of famous names including Mark Twain, President Ulysses S Grant and JP Morgan, has no dedicated accommodation manager, so guests sometimes struggle to receive the attention they need and end up feeling the hotel has become an afterthought beside the noisy saloon.(n)

programme.title: SAS: Who Dares Wins
programme.desc: Chief instructor Ant and his team test whether the 17 remaining recruits can control their aggression, pitting them against one another in a bout of sparring and a brutal game of murderball. In 35C heat and 90 per cent humidity, the volunteers endure a fearsome jungle `sickener' - a non-stop series of exercises that only finishes when four recruits withdraw.(n)

programme.title: Food Unwrapped
programme.desc: Jimmy Doherty heads to Sicily, where a vast network of tunnels leads to a subterranean salt-processing plant. Kate Quilton looks at free range hens, and is surprised to learn that most chicks on British farms have their beaks trimmed at birth. In the Netherlands, she visits a new cutting-edge farm designed using the latest scientific advances in hen welfare. Plus, in Scotland, Matt Tebbutt makes a surprising discovery about the origins of haggis, and then faces the ordeal of delivering some unwelcome news to an unsuspecting audience.(n)

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces
programme.desc: The architect meets Ian and Becky from Lincolnshire, who are embarking on the restoration of a rare VW Phoenix campervan. But this couple are not doing things by halves, having decided to add a sound-activated dance floor to the vehicle. He also visits Stirlingshire, where a small family business plans to convert a Sea King helicopter into luxury overnight accommodation, and travels to an ordinary residential street on the outskirts of Auckland, New Zealand, to see a dome home that is out of this world. Plus, George and Will design a front door for their rotating house.(n)

programme.title: Be Your Own Doctor
programme.desc: Kate Quilton is joined by Dr Tamal Ray - known for his time on The Great British Bake Off last year - to investigate a series of questions about health, examining the latest online solutions to pressing medical needs and testing the boldest claims from recent advice. They examine whether eating placenta after childbirth can really revitalise the body faster, look at an app offering guidance on the status of moles and sun damage and try to discover what coconut pulling has to do with the perfect smile.(n)

programme.title: Grand Designs
programme.desc: Simon and Jasmine Dale take on the challenging task of building a 21st-century, low-impact three-bedroom family home with a budget of only £500. As part of a pioneering, government-backed, sustainable village called Lammas, the couple must adhere to their fierce planning conditions of self-sufficiency or risk losing everything.(n)

programme.title: Hoarder SOS
programme.desc: A costume maker from Chester needs help as her house is crammed with fabric, and in Perth, a mum of four gets help from her children to reclaim her home of clutter.(n)

programme.title: Phil Spencer: Secret Agent
programme.desc: Phil visits Stamford, Lincolnshire, where Mark and Tina Harrison's three-bedroom home needs a revamp to help it appeal to younger buyers. He also discovers a house that is being pitched at the family market with no success. It has the right size, a decent garden and a good location, but with stains on almost every carpet, the owners need to put a lot of work into it. Can the expert turn both properties around in just one week?.(n)

programme.title: Phil Spencer: Secret Agent

programme.title: Friday the 13th Part VIII: Jason Takes Manhattan
programme.desc: The body count continues to rise in Friday the 13th Part VIII: Jason Takes Manhattan -- although Jason doesn't take Manhattan until a good hour into the movie. The film begins, once again at Camp Crystal Lake, where two young goofs throw an anchor into a submerged power cable. The electrical jolt revives the ever popular and resolute maniacal killer Jason Vorhees. After dispatching the two idiots, Jason latches onto a rundown freighter, passing as a cruise ship called the Lazarus, where the Crystal Lake High School seniors are celebrating their senior trip by sailing to New York City. Like a kid in a candy store, Jason takes advantage of the close quarters of the freighter by attacking and killing an assortment of high-school slasher movie stereotypes. By the time the boat reaches Manhattan, the radio is dead along with most of the people. The survivors swim ashore to escape the mad killer. But Jason tags along behind them, eager to sink his teeth into The Big Apple(n)

programme.title: Howard the Duck
programme.desc: Director and co-screenwriter Willard Huyck has taken Steve Garber's abrasive, beer-drinking and cigar-smoking comic-book character and castrated him, turning him into a wide-eyed cutesy-pie available for the toy shelves. Huyck's Howard the Duck is a being from outer space, blown into Cleveland by an errant laser beam. After a few minutes on Earth, Howard runs into rock singer Beverly Switzler (Lea Thompson), and they become fast friends after Howard protects her from a couple of nasty punkers. The film then degenerates into an extended chase, as Howard and Beverly are pursued by government agents who want to capture Howard before he can be beamed back into space(n)

Ants develop super intelligence and kill the two scientists sent to study them. Sci-fi horror(n)

programme.title: Frank Miller's Sin City
programme.desc: A collection of interweaving stories all based in the corrupt, crime infested hell-hole that is Basin City. Heavily influenced by film-noir, the main storylines concern a hulking brute called Marv, who is seeking the murderer of a beautiful woman who was killed while asleep in bed with him, a photographer called Dwight who is callously used and seeks revenge, and a soon-to-be-retiring policeman called Hartigan(n)

programme.title: Hero
programme.desc: Petty thief Bernie, stumbling upon a plane crash, grudgingly steps in and rescues the survivors, one of whom is ace reporter Gale Gayley. After losing one of his shoes at the scene of the accident, Bernie gives the other one to down-and-out Bubber, but when Gale tries to track down her heroic saviour using the shoe as a clue, Bubber sees his chance to cash in on the $1 million reward(n)

programme.title: Batman

programme.title: The Longest Ride
programme.desc: A star-crossed love affair begins between a retired bull rider who wants to get back in the saddle and an art student preparing to seek her fortune in New York City. As their relationship is put to the ultimate test, the wisdom of an aging man who recalls his own lost love serves as a source of great inspiration(n)

programme.title: Crimson Tide
programme.desc: A radical group has seized control of a nuclear missile base and the USS Alabama, a state-of-the-art nuclear submarine, has been ordered into action in this taut thriller. But when a fragmented message arrives onboard to launch a defensive strike against the enemy, suddenly a fiery battle of wills erupts between the veteran sub commander - who never questions orders - and his more cautious second officer, who can't help but suspect a command to start a nuclear war. Gene Hackman and Denzel Washington star(n)

programme.title: Formula 51
programme.desc: Samuel L Jackson plays a pharmaceutical genius who has used his knowledge to make a fortune in illegal drugs, particularly with Formula 51, named after its potency above heroin, crack, anything. But instead of selling it to his drug lord employer, he jets to Liverpool where Robert Carlyle is acting as broker for Ricky Tomlinson, who's prepared to offer $20m for the formula - money Jackson would love to spend if he can stay alive long enough in Ronny Yu's fast moving crime thriller(n)

programme.title: Hitman
programme.desc: An international assassin known only as Agent 47 (Timothy Olyphant) carries out high-profile hits for a mysterious organization known only as "The Agency" in this adaptation of the popular Eidos Interactive video-game series. Agent 47 is an elite, genetically engineered assassin who takes great pride in his work. His lethal grace, steady shot, and unparalleled precision have all served to make him one of the most sought-after assassins in the world. But when the killer without a conscience is faced with an unanticipated series of developments, his entire perception of reality begins to shift. On assignment to take out Russian head of state Belicoff (Ulrich Thomsen), Agent 47 is caught off guard by the appearance of presidential look-alikes. When the high-profile hit captures the attention of such powerful intelligence organizations as the CIA and Interpol, agent Mike Whittier (Dougray Scott) is dispatched to rein Agent 47 in. Meanwhile, a mysterious Russian prostitute named Nika (Olga Kurylenko) has walked into Agent 47's life, causing the methodical killer to become overwhelmed by emotions that were previously foreign to him(n)

programme.title: Run All Night

Matt finds out about the county's pear cider industry, helping with a harvest and visiting some of the world's oldest pear trees in Hellen's Manor, while Anita meets a traditional clog maker and explores the history of a farm. Joe Crowley meets a student documenting birds, Tom Heap delves into the history of working at sea, and Adam Henson harvests bracken for fuel on the farm. Including weather for the week ahead.(n)

programme.title: Strictly Come Dancing
programme.desc: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman present the results of last night's Halloween special, revealing which of the 10 remaining couples have received the fewest votes and will face each other in the dance-off, their fates in the hands of judges Len Goodman, Bruno Tonioli, Craig Revel Horwood and Darcey Bussell. There is also a song from Laura Mvula.(n)

programme.title: Antiques Roadshow
programme.desc: Fiona Bruce presents a special episode from on board the Flying Scotsman during its journey across Cumbria and Yorkshire, with passengers sharing family stories from the early history of long-distance travel. Artefacts brought on board to be valued include a porthole from the wreck of ocean liner RMS Lusitania, designer cutlery from Concorde, and an iron bar that was once part of the famous train.(n)

programme.title: Poldark
programme.desc: Demelza refuses to speak to Ross, assuming that he will abandon her and return to Elizabeth. At Sir Hugh Bodregun's ball, she turns to Captain McNeil for support, and invites him to her room. George rides to Trenwith to talk Elizabeth out of cancelling their wedding, while Ross's fortunes seem to be changing for the better, with the offer of a prospering shipbuilding partnership from Tonkin, while Henshawe comes across the richest lode of tin he has ever seen when the mine clearance is completed.(n)

programme.title: Match of the Day 2
programme.desc: Mark Chapman presents the day's Premier League highlights, including Everton v West Ham United at Goodison Park, and Southampton v Chelsea at St Mary's Stadium. Plus, a round-up of all the goals and talking points from yesterday's matches.(n)

programme.title: The Women's Football Show
programme.desc: A round-up of the final weekend in the FA WSL season, which saw champions Manchester City Women host Birmingham City Ladies. Presented by Tina Daheley.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: They Knew What They Wanted
programme.desc: A vineyard owner exchanges letters with a waitress, but sends her a photograph of his handsome foreman. When they finally meet, she agrees to marry him despite his dishonesty. However, following a disastrous accident, she becomes tempted by the prospect of an affair with the man whose picture she received. Drama, starring Carole Lombard, Charles Laughton and William Gargan.(n)

programme.title: Mr and Mrs Smith
programme.desc: A couple's rather dull life together is turned upside-down by a bureaucratic decision which renders their marriage null and void - prompting them to attempt to outdo each other in their newfound freedom. Alfred Hitchcock's romantic comedy, with Carole Lombard, Robert Montgomery, Gene Raymond and Jack Carson.(n)

programme.title: Coast
programme.desc: Nicholas Crane tells the tale of the Great Storm of 1703, which saw ships blown from British shores to Norway, while Ian McMillan discusses the fate of hospital ship Rohilla, which ran aground off Whitby, North Yorkshire, in 1914. Dick Strawbridge visits Tiree in the Inner Hebrides, where he explains how the timings of the D-Day landings were determined by RAF weather forecasters.(n)

programme.title: Secret Britain
programme.desc: Matt Baker and Julia Bradbury travel across Britain in search of forgotten and rarely visited areas of natural beauty, beginning with a journey from south-west England to Dover. Although their route passes through some of Britain's most crowded areas, they still discover hidden treasures, including the ancient roads of Dorset and the nation's only desert.(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Developers Lucy Alexander and Martin Roberts explore properties about to be auctioned in Oldham, Cardiff and Kilburn in north-west London - then follow the sale and talk to the buyers about their plans for the buildings. They later return to find out how the new owners have progressed.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: It's finals week as the winners of the regional heats do battle to get their dishes on the menu for the banquet at the Palace of Westminster in celebration of ordinary people honoured by the Queen. The chefs begins with the starter course, with Matthew Fort, Oliver Peyton and Prue Leith joined by guest judge Claire MacDonald.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The finalists prepare their seafood courses and those chefs who didn't make it onto the shortlist with their starters are hoping to do better this time. Judges Oliver Peyton, Prue Leith and Matthew Fort are joined by food writer Tim Hayward, who helped judge the Scotland heat of the contest.(n)

programme.title: Vertigo
programme.desc: A private eye with an aversion to heights is hired to trail the wife of an old college friend because of her strange and inconsistent behaviour. However, he soon falls obsessively in love with her, and is drawn into a complex and destructive mystery. Alfred Hitchcock's thriller, starring Kim Novak in a dual role alongside James Stewart, Barbara Bel Geddes and Tom Helmore.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off: An Extra Slice
programme.desc: Jo Brand chats to this year's winner in the aftermath of the grand final, and is also joined by the other 11 contestants. Mary Berry provides an insight into how she and Paul Hollywood made their choice. Plus, a look back at unseen footage from the show and the best and worst viewers' bakes.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Thomas Plant and Michael Baggott value items in Cirencester, Gloucestershire, including a 200-year-old teapot and costume jewellery encrusted with real diamonds. Paul Martin vists a 400-year-old house where even the cobwebs are being preserved for future generations.(n)

programme.title: National Treasure
programme.desc: An intrepid treasure-hunter follows a series of ingenious clues in a perilous quest to track down a war chest hidden by America's founding fathers generations before. He has to contend with determined rivals in the shape of a treacherous associate and the FBI. Action adventure, starring Nicolas Cage, Diane Kruger, Sean Bean and Justin Bartha.(n)

programme.title: Don't Panic! The Dad's Army Story
programme.desc: Victoria Wood celebrates Jimmy Perry and David Croft's comedy about the misadventures of a Home Guard platoon during the Second World War. Featuring clips of classic scenes, footage of the cast on location and reminiscences about the making of the series from stars of the show including Ian Lavender (Private Pike), Clive Dunn (Lance-Corporal Jones) and Bill Pertwee (ARP Warden Hodges).(n)

programme.title: Dad's Army
programme.desc: Doctor McCeavedy accidentally discovers that Frazer keeps a hoard of gold sovereigns in his home and Mainwaring tries to persuade the undertaker that his life savings would be better kept in a safer place - namely his bank. Vintage comedy, with Arthur Lowe and John Laurie. First shown in 1977.(n)

programme.title: Artsnight
programme.sub-title: Artsnight: 2016 - The Year of King Lear.
programme.desc: A look at how Shakespeare's play resonates with contemporary audiences and why it is regarded as one of the playwright's greatest accomplishments. The programme examines five major productions being staged across the UK during 2016, and features contributions from actors Diana Rigg, Timothy West and Antony Sher, and director Nicholas Hytner.(n)

programme.title: Imagine
programme.sub-title: Imagine: The Seven Killings of Marlon James.
programme.desc: Alan Yentob meets the award-winning author, who became the first Jamaican writer to win the Man Booker prize in 2015 for his novel A Brief History of Seven Killings, and subsequently came out as gay in an article for the New York Times. Alan accompanies him on a return trip to his home country, and investigates how his three novels provide an insight into the nation's history.(n)

programme.title: The Harder They Come
programme.desc: Reggae legend Jimmy Cliff stars in this poignant Jamaican drama about a naive country boy who visits Kingston in search of reggae stardom, only to get involved in the shady world of drug dealing as his musical career takes off. With no other option but to go on the run, he fights back against the system which forced him into a life of crime and becomes a political hero in the process. With Janet Barkley, Carl Bradshaw and Bob Charlton.(n)

programme.title: A Very British Murder with Lucy Worsley
programme.desc: The historian tells the story of one of the first high-profile killers - Dr Crippen, who was hanged in 1910 for poisoning and dismembering his wife - before turning her attention to the interwar period, when detective fiction reached the peak of its popularity at the hands of authors Agatha Christie and Dorothy L Sayers. After undergoing the elaborate initiation ceremony of the Detection Club, which was set up by a group of British writers in 1930, Lucy considers how Alfred Hitchcock's films and Graham Greene's books eclipsed the traditional murder-mystery story in the depiction of homicide.(n)

programme.title: Witchfinder General
programme.desc: A lawyer callously destroys innocent lives while performing his duties as a witchfinder, earning a terrifying reputation for brutality and injustice. However, he meets his match in a courageous soldier seeking revenge on the man for having raped his betrothed. Michael Reeves' 17th-century period horror, with Vincent Price, Ian Ogilvy, Rupert Davies, Patrick Wymark and Hilary Dwyer.(n)

programme.title: (GMT) The Curse of Frankenstein (1957)
programme.desc: An obsessive scientist is determined to create life and builds a creature using parts taken from various corpses. He succeeds in animating the monster, but its brain is damaged in the process, driving it mad and causing it to embark on a killing spree. The first in Hammer's series of horror films inspired by Mary Shelley's novel, starring Peter Cushing and Christopher Lee.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: The A to Z of TV Gardening
programme.desc: Carol Kirkwood looks at subjects beginning with the letter L as she continues her alphabetical journey through the world of horticulture. Along the way, she gets inspiration and advice from some of the BBC's most popular gardening presenters.(n)

programme.title: Glorious Gardens from Above
programme.desc: Horticulturist Christine Walkden visits the gardens of Staffordshire, taking to the water to remove some unwanted pests at Biddulph Grange, and trying out tree-hugging at Shugborough Hall. Plus, how the area's industrial heritage shaped the county's landscape.(n)

programme.title: Life in a Cottage Garden with Carol Klein
programme.desc: The horticulturist presents a year-long diary about the life cycle of her garden at Glebe Cottage in Devon, where she offers seasonal advice and guidance, beginning with how to look after plants throughout January and February. She prunes the greenery, prepares the soil and plants garlic, before a local woodsman helps her lay a native hedge.(n)

programme.title: Greatest Gardens
programme.desc: Diarmuid Gavin and Helen Dillon tour Northern Irish gardens. In this first episode, the presenters are in County Down and Antrim, where they cast their eyes over a compartmentalised paradise behind a Georgian terrace in Hillsborough, a reclaimed Carrowdore quarry, and am ambitious river landscape in the shadow of a modern rural dwelling. At the end, the pair decide which they liked best.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Anita Rani visits a commercial walnut harvest in Somerset, while Matt Baker meets a man in East Sussex who spent six months living off grid in a tree house made of recycled wood. A botanist reveals how he uses time-lapse filming to record fungi growing, Naomi Wilkinson discovers how conkers became a valuable resource during the First World War, and chef Cyrus Todiwala prepares Indian style sausages using rare breed woodland pork.(n)

programme.title: The Beechgrove Garden
programme.desc: For the end of the run, the presenters pack in as many tips to keep green-fingered viewers going throughout the winter, while also making plans for spring. George Anderson and Jim McColl are in the fruit cage, taking stock and doing some remedial work. Carole Baxter is starting her Christmas wrapping early, demonstrating how to cover tender plants that need extra protection. She also visits Huntly Cot near Temple, Midlothian, which has at its centre a heart-shaped garden with a natural spring burn, perfectly in tune with the moorland setting. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Best Bites
programme.desc: John Torode presents highlights from throughout the series, offering viewers a chance to revisit some of their favourite moments from previous years in the kitchen.(n)

programme.title: Food & Drink
programme.desc: Michel Roux Jr and resident drinks expert Kate Goodman are joined by cook and food writer Rachel Khoo to create the perfect luxury dish to make when entertaining friends. Restaurateur Oliver Peyton tries a new food experience that leaves him cold and blogger and supper club entrepreneur Kerstin Rodgers shares her secrets for a successful dinner party. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: MOTD2 Extra
programme.desc: Mark Chapman presents football discussion with a line-up of guests, focusing on yesterday's matches and news ahead of today's fixtures, which include Everton v West Ham United.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The finalists prepare their main courses, hoping to impress with some new and untested dishes. Judges Matthew Fort, Prue Leith and Oliver Peyton are joined by guest judge John Williams, Executive Chef of The Ritz, as they decide who has done enough to take their main course to the banquet. The day ends in disappointment for one chef as timings ruin what could have been a winning dish.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: Killer Whales: Beneath the Surface - Natural World.
programme.desc: A look at research into the lives of the marine mammals, which were long regarded as fearsome predators until the first one was brought into captivity for study in 1964, revealing facts about their profound intelligence, social interactions and parental instincts. The programme illustrates how contemporary studies continue to unearth revelations about the whales' behaviour.(n)

programme.title: Heir Hunters
programme.desc: The researchers investigate the case of a famous Blackpool accordion player, and reveal a tragic tale of separation involving two brothers who died on the same day in the same hospital after not seeing each other for many years. Plus, the team explores the history of Rolls-Royce and the Crewe railways, before sharing details of other unclaimed estates.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: The team heads to Dudley in the West Midlands, where Paul Martin gets his hands on an unusual piece of marine taxidermy that has been sat gathering dust in a cupboard. Adam Partridge picks up some napkin rings that he hopes will dazzle the bidders, and Thomas Plant plans to attract big bids for a train set. Plus, Paul heads to the Dudley Museum and Art Gallery to get an insight into the work of artist Percy Shakespeare.(n)

programme.title: Frankenweenie
programme.desc: A lonely boy uses electricity to bring his dead dog back to life. However, the presence of the animal in the neighbourhood leads to panic over a monster, while the young scientist's classmates are soon also meddling with life and death to revive their own pets. Tim Burton's stop-motion animated fantasy, with the voices of Charlie Tahan and Winona Ryder.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Classroom Heroes
programme.desc: Hugh Dennis hosts the awards ceremony honouring Britain's best teachers from the Guildhall in the City of London, featuring a selection of surprise celebrity guests.(n)

programme.title: Inside Obama's White House
programme.desc: Examining how Barack Obama set out to end George Bush's wars in the Middle East and reset relations with the rest of the world. In Syria, when evidence shows the use of chemical weapons, Obama decides to bomb. But when the British Parliament votes against the intervention, he decides he needs the backing of a reluctant Congress. Foreign Secretary William Hague explains why the British Parliament voted against intervention in 2013. This episode also explores how Obama scored a big win when he negotiated a secret deal to end the nuclear threat from Iran - behind the backs of his closest allies.(n)

programme.title: Coast
programme.sub-title: Coast: The Great Guide: The Heart of England's South Coast.
programme.desc: Neil Oliver and Tessa Dunlop present a guide to England's South Coast from Brighton to Chesil, revealing what makes these two pebble beaches special. Neil also takes a trip on a flotilla of boats that includes a prototype yacht being prepared for the America's Cup, a vessel designed to help save the Solent oyster population and an offshore powerboat. Plus, a round-up of the best Coast stories from the past 10 years.(n)

programme.title: Operation Gold Rush with Dan Snow
programme.desc: New series. The historian recreates the 19th-century Klondike Gold Rush, attempting to find riches in a remote region on the edge of the Canadian arctic. He is joined on his expedition by polar explorer Felicity Aston and medic Dr Kevin Fong. The first challenge of the trek is to cross Alaska's Coast Mountains, where they retrace two routes set by 19th-century miners and brave icy rivers, avalanche-prone slopes and near vertical ascents.(n)

programme.title: Nigel Farage Gets His Life Back
programme.desc: Satirical comedy, starring Kevin Bishop as the UKIP leader. A fly-on-the-wall documentary crew follow Farage in the aftermath of the EU referendum and his subsequent resignation as leader of UKIP, claiming that he wants to return to normal life. Adamant that he does not miss the limelight and never wanted to be prime minister, Farage tries to adjust to a routine away from the public eye, filling his days with television, trips to the pub, a new friend in the shape of Donald Trump, and the fresh challenge of growing a moustache.(n)

programme.title: Mock the Week
programme.desc: James Acaster, Rob Beckett, Gary Delaney, Elis James and Sara Pascoe join host Dara O Briain and regular participant Hugh Dennis for the topical comedy show, looking back at the week's events through the medium of fast-thinking and improvisation.(n)

programme.title: QI XL
programme.desc: Extended episode of the panel show, in which Sandi Toksvig invites Lucy Beaumont, Jason Manford, Rhod Gilbert and Alan Davies to answer questions on subjects associated with the North and the Norse. Since the questions are impossible to answer, points are awarded for being interesting rather than correct.(n)

programme.title: Let Me In
programme.desc: A bullied 12-year-old boy befriends a mysterious girl who has recently arrived in his neighbourhood. He is unaware she is a vampire, and is responsible for a recent series of killings. When the girl's human protector disappears, she is forced to turn to her new friend for help. Remake of Swedish horror Let the Right One In, starring Chloe Grace Moretz and Kodi Smit-McPhee.(n)

programme.title: Timeshift
programme.sub-title: Sailors, Ships and Stevedores: The Story of British Docks.
programme.desc: The transformation of British docks, many of which have changed from commercial portals to the world into clean, contemporary hubs for leisure and the arts. Narrated by Sue Johnston.(n)

programme.title: The Incredible Human Journey
programme.desc: Dr Alice Roberts examines the journey of mankind's ancestors from Africa to Europe, how homo sapiens managed to survive the harsh ice age conditions and their relationship with the native inhabitants of the continent - the Neanderthals, who had bigger brains and were better adapted to the cold. She explores the theory that competition between the two species led to the extinction of the former and the factors that governed subsequent changes in skin colour.(n)

programme.title: The Code
programme.desc: Racing to save Papua Independence leader Remsey from false imprisonment and find Callum before it's too late, Jesse and Roth forge an unlikely alliance. Ned reaches out to an undercover photojournalist to help locate Jesse. Australian thriller, starring Ashley Zukerman, Anthony LaPaglia, Greg Kapernick and Dan Spielman.(n)

programme.title: The Code
programme.desc: Jesse has to lie to Roth to save his own skin and that of Hani's father, and with political tensions high, a rally turns ugly as Jesse desperately tries to decrypt the files. Australian thriller, starring Ashley Zukerman, Anthony LaPaglia, Dan Spielman and Adele Perovic.(n)

programme.title: The Kate Bush Story: Running Up That Hill
programme.desc: Documentary exploring the singer-songwriter's career and music from her 1978 debut single Wuthering Heights to her 2011 album 50 Words for Snow with testimony from collaborators, fellow artists inspired by her work and fans. Featuring David Gilmour, the guitarist who discovered Bush, as well as Peter Gabriel, Elton John, Stephen Fry, Outkast's Big Boi and Steve Coogan.(n)

programme.title: Kate Bush at the BBC
programme.desc: A compilation of the singer's performances at the BBC's studios between 1978 and 1994. Bush appeared on a variety of programmes, including Top of the Pops, Wogan, Ask Aspel, Saturday Night at the Mill and the Leo Sayer Show. Featuring the hits Wuthering Heights, Babooshka, Running Up That Hill and Hounds of Love, as well as intriguing and lesser-known material.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: David Jensen presents the edition from July 8, featuring music by Captain Sensible, Bananarama, Imagination, Irene Cara, Odyssey, Bucks Fizz and the Steve Miller Band.(n)

programme.desc: Documentary exploring the singer-songwriter's career and music from her 1978 debut single Wuthering Heights to her 2011 album 50 Words for Snow with testimony from collaborators, fellow artists inspired by her work and fans. programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: Includes appearances from Hot Chocolate, Dexys Midnight Runners, Cliff Richard, David Essex, Japan, Visage and Irene Cara.(n)

programme.title: Canals - The Making of a Nation
programme.desc: Liz McIvor tells the story of the people who operated the canal boats, carrying fuel and goods around the country. During the Victorian era they gained reputations for criminality, violence and drinking, but was such a reputation deserved? Liz discovers grisly canal crimes, investigates health and welfare on-board working boats, and looks at why canal children were last on the list to be offered safeguards and formal education. She reveals the campaigners who set out to tackle this injustice, including George Smith of Coalville, Leicestershire, and Sister Mary Ward of Stoke Bruerne, Northamptonshire.(n)

programme.title: Books That Made Britain
programme.sub-title: East Anglia: The Scene of the Crime.
programme.desc: Martha Kearney investigates why East Anglia has inspired so many great crime writers, including PD James and Nicci French.(n)

programme.title: Frankenstein from The Royal Ballet
programme.desc: Darcey Bussell and Ore Oduba introduce a new production by the Royal Ballet inspired by Mary Shelley's novel, featuring original music by Lowell Liebermann and choreography by artist-in-residence Liam Scarlett. Starring Federico Bonelli as the misguided scientist, Steven McRae as his tragic creation, and Laura Morera as Frankenstein's fiancee Elizabeth.(n)

programme.title: Annabel's Nightclub: A String of Naked Lightbulbs
programme.desc: Documentary charting the 50-year history of London's first members-only nightclub. The venue, situated at 44 Berkeley Square, has long been considered the exclusive haunt of Britain's most celebrated public figures. Annabel's remains the only nightclub to have been visited by the Queen, and once courted notoriety by refusing entry to The Beatles. This film explores the club's story from inception to the present day, revealing how membership over the years also serves as a cultural biopsy of London since the Second World War.(n)

programme.title: The Long Hot Summer
programme.desc: The made-for-TV The Long Hot Summer was based on the 1958 theatrical film of the same name-which, in turn, was based on two William Faulkner short stories. Don Johnson plays Ben Quick, a Southern drifter who is under suspicion as a "barn burner." Ben secures a job at the Mississippi mansion of town-boss Will Varner (Jason Robards). Varner's daughter Noel (Judith Ivey) and daughter-in-law Eula (Cybill Shepherd) vie for the handsome Ben's attention, while the patriarch's weakling son Jody (William Russ) seethes. When a few local barns are burned, Ben is the primary suspect-and no one is more suspicious than Noel. A murder trial and lynch mob both figure into the second half of the two-part The Long Hot Summer; the film originally aired October 6 and 7, 1985(n)

programme.title: Sweet Dreams
programme.desc: Sweet Dreams stars Jessica Lange as country-western singer Patsy Cline, whose tragic death in 1963 cut short one of the most fabulous success stories in the annals of popular music. Robert Getchell's screenplay goes the usual route of contrasting Cline's rise to fame in the years between 1956 and 1963 with her turbulent private life. As the wife of hard-drinking Charlie Dick (Ed Harris),Cline is subjected to all manner of abuse and humiliation, yet she stays with Charlie long beyond normal human endurance. A happy second marriage is all too short-lived--as is Cline herself. While the Cline-Dick relationship is presented relatively realistically, the film makes a number of chronological errors concerning Cline's "public" life. Also: how can anyone know what was being said in the last horrifying seconds before Cline's fatal plane crash? Unlike its role model Coal Miner's Daughter (in which Beverly D'Angelo played Cline), Sweet Dreams does not feature the voice of its star during the musical scenes; instead, actual recordings of Patsy Cline, electronically enhanced to match modern technology, are heard on the soundtrack. Song highlights include "Crazy," "I Fall to Pieces," and the title tune(n)

programme.desc: Body of Evidence: The Tom Capano Trial. A&E investigates the deadly consequences of unrequited love in the one-hour American Justice: Body of Evidence -- The Tom Capano Trial. Wealthy and well-connected, Tom Capano was still subjected to the torments of the heart. When an affair with Anne Marie Fahey ended badly, he snapped. After murdering his ex-lover, Capano dumped her body in the water, a seemingly clever move. However, Capano never counted on the guilty conscience of his own brother to secure his undoing. The police kept the jealous boyfriend under surveillance until they had the sibling's confession as accomplice. Surprisingly, at trial, Capano himself admitted to removing the body. But, he held onto the claim that Fahey was killed by someone else. Capano was convicted and sentenced to death(n)

programme.sub-title: Crime of Passion: The Pamela Smart Story
programme.desc: Crime of Passion: The Pamela Smart Story. Youth, seduction, and violence populate the landscape of the A&E program American Justice: Crimes of Passion -- The Pamela Smart Story. As an attractive motivated schoolteacher, Pam Smart was carving out a successful middle-class life. But, inwardly, she was passionately dissatisfied. Her husband held her back, yet she couldn't afford to live alone. Then, Smart met teenager Bill Flynn. He fell for her and she seemed flattered by the attention. Eventually, their relationship became intimate and Smart found the answer to all her problems. Through manipulation and claims of abuse, she convinced her young lover to kill her husband and that's just what he did with the help of two friends. But, Smart's calculating manner gave her away when police suspected her of being less than grief-stricken. What followed was the first live broadcast trial in history. The media explosion surrounding the case was unparalleled. Smart turned out to be a lot less organized than she thought. When her killers caved and word got around of her arranged hit, she was doomed. A&E takes the viewer back to the original trial of the century(n)

programme.title: The Fly
programme.desc: Wealthy Helene Delambre (Patricia Owens) is discovered late at night in the factory owned by her husband Andre (David Hedison). Helene stands beside a huge metal press, which has crushed the head and arm of her husband. Held for murder, the near-catatonic Helene refuses to tell anyone--not even Andre's brother Francois (Vincent Price)--why she did it. Francois cannot help but notice that Helene reacts in mortal terror when a tiny flies zips through the room. Nor can he disregard the statement made by Helene's son Philippe (Charles Herbert) that the fly has a curious white head and leg. When Francois pretends that he's captured the fly, Helene relaxes enough to tell her story. It seems that Andre, a scientist, had been working on a matter transmitter, which he claimed could disintegrate matter, then reintegrate it elsewhere. After a few experiments, Andre tried the transmitter himself. Just as he stepped into the disintegration chamber, a fly also flew into the chamber. We aren't immediately shown the results of this, save for the fact that Andre afterward insists upon keeping his head and arm covered. Alone with her husband, Helene abruptly removes the covering, revealing that Andre now bears the head of a fly! His atoms have become mixed up with the fly, and now he is unable to reverse the procedure. Deciding that his transmitter will be a bogy rather than a blessing to mankind, Andre smashes the apparatus and burns his notes. He then instructs Helene, via body language, to crush his fly-like head and arm in the press. Neither Francois nor inspector Charas (Herbert Marshall) believe the story...until, while staring intently at a spider's web in the garden, they see a tiny entrapped fly with Andre's head and arm, tinnily screaming "Help me! Help me!" as the slavering spider approaches (If you're wondering why Vincent Price and Herbert Marshall do not look one another in the eye during this scene, it is because they couldn't deliver their dialogue without dissolving into laughter). Infinitely subtler than the admittedly excellent 1986 remake, the 1958 The Fly is one of the definitive big-budget horror films of its decade. Best bit: the prismatic "fly's eye view" of the screaming Patricia Owens. The Fly was adapted from George Langelaan's short story by James (Shogun) Clavell(n)

programme.desc: For 60 years, a mysterious nameless monk zigzagged the globe to protect an ancient scroll that grants remarkable powers to those who possess it. But now the monk must find someone new to assume the responsibility. As fate would have it, the new caretaker turns out to be a scruffy and distinctly non-enlightened petty thief named Kar. But when he inadvertently saves the Bulletproof Monk from capture, the two become partners in a scheme to save the world from the scroll's most avid pursuer. In the mission, they are aided by a beautiful Russian mob affiliate with amazing martial arts skills and a vested interest in keeping the scroll in virtuous hands(n)

programme.title: Extreme Measures
programme.desc: Intelligent thriller about an idealistic young doctor (Hugh Grant) who uncovers a sinister world of illegal medical experiments. Dr Guy Luthan (Grant) is working through another hard shift in the emergency room when he treats a delusional, homeless patient who exhibits wildly erratic and unfamiliar symptoms. To add to the mystery, the man is naked, except for a medical bracelet on his wrist that can only have come from another hospital. Luthan is unable to save the patient, but neither can he forget the unusual circumstances surrounding the man's arrival. He resolves to look into the case further, but when he looks for the autopsy report he finds that it is missing - and so is the body. Unwilling to let the matter drop, despite strong urging from his superiors at the hospital, Luthan continues to search for answers. As this search progresses, he experiences more bad 'luck': his apartment is broken into and he is loses his job. Clearly somebody wants him to stop his investigation. Undeterred, Luthan pursues the truth, and the trail leads to internationally renowned neurologist Dr. Lawrence Myrick (Gene Hackman), acclaimed for his research into regenerating spinal tissue. Myrick's research has the potential to change the world for countless victims of spinal injury - but does this excuse the terrible price being paid by innocent victims?(n)

programme.title: Flight of the Phoenix
programme.desc: Based on a novel by Elleston Trevor, director John Moore's The Flight of the Phoenix is a remake of a 1965 film of the same name starring film icon James Stewart. The story revolves around the plight of Captain Frank Towns (Dennis Quaid), a pilot whose C-119 cargo plane full of oil workers could not withstand the violent winds of a desert sandstorm. Stranded in the harsh terrain of Mongolia's Gobi Desert (a departure from the original, in which the plane crashed in the Sahara), Frank and his navigator face an equal challenge in maintaining order among the survivors. The group of oilmen had planned on an uneventful trip to shut off a group of rigs falling below their productivity expectations -- not fending for their very lives. Before long, some men are revealed as cowards, while others exhibit a surprising show of strength, all the while hoping that the wreckage of the original plane can be salvaged before a Lord of the Flies situation occurs. Miranda Otto is featured in a supporting role, as well as Giovanni Ribisi and Tyrese Gibson(n)

programme.desc: Eames and Goren's investigation into the murder of a pharmaceutical salesman found cut in half uncovers a web of corruption involving fraud, bribery, identity theft and a conspiracy to sell contaminated blood. Detective drama, starring Vincent D'Onofrio and Kathryn Erbe.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: The driver of a Ferrari is gunned down by a motorcyclist and the victim is identified as petty officer Colin Boxer, who was holding down a second job as a valet parker and had borrowed the sports car. The owner of the vehicle turns out to be Vijay Chaya, the billionaire head of a large corporation, and the team suspects a case of mistaken identity. During the course of the investigation, Gibbs chances on a medal awarded to Leroy Jethro Moore, the man he was named after and an estranged friend of his father. Guest starring Billy Dee Williams (The Empire Strikes Back) and Ralph Waite (The Waltons).(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Part one of two. First lieutenant Michael Torres gets involved in a fight before falling to the ground, and is found beaten to death the next morning. The only witness is his friend and colleague Captain Joe Westcott, who suffers from post-traumatic stress disorder and has trouble distinguishing reality from his past military experiences in the Middle East.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Part two of two. Tony reviews satellite footage of rebel forces in the Middle East and spots Kersey among a group of insurgents, concluding that Joe Westcott's fear of him was well-founded. Back at HQ, Abby creates a 3D computer model of the attack that occurred in Afghanistan and Joe dons a virtual-reality headset to relive the traumatic events. Will it jog his memory?.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Teenager Lydia Wade manages to escape a gang of masked men trying to abduct her and her friend Rosie, the daughter of a US Navy commander. Lydia's Navy captain father David Wade was shot dead during the attack and her mother is overseas, so Ziva offers to look after the girl, while Abby tries to jog her memory by creating facial reconstructions of the attackers based on some grainy CCTV footage. DiNozzo and McGee find links on Rosie's laptop to possible suspect John `Diesel' Stevens.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Gibbs is called to the scene when there is an attempt on the life of FBI agent TC Fornell, with the assailant identified as Navy seaman Tyler Brown. The pair team up and visit the bar where Brown worked and bump into their mutual ex-wife Diane Sterling, who was operating undercover as an employee suspected of stealing customers' identities. Joe Spano and Melinda McGraw guest star.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: A day spent working on a cut-and-dried case leaves the team free to spend some time away from work, and while McGee and Delilah argue over the importance of keeping shop-talk to a minimum, DiNozzo ends up boring his dinner date with crime-solving tales. However, the agents' personal plans are all interrupted as, one-by-one, they realise errors have been made in closing their latest investigation. Starring Mark Harmon, David McCallum and Pauley Perrette.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: A US Navy Public Affairs Officer is killed, and when the team takes up the case, both the man's wife and his mistress emerge as potential suspects. Each woman offering a very different take on the chain of events that led to the murder, and the investigators are forced to decide which of the two is telling the truth. Meanwhile, DiNozzo's father comes to the aid of a homeless woman, who makes a surprising claim about his relationship with her. Guest starring Robert Wagner.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: An architect is found dead at his mansion by a police officer who claims a ghost could have had some involvement in the murder. The team investigates conventional leads, while Jane concentrates on pursuing the supernatural angle, discovering there is rumoured to be treasure hidden in the building. Elsewhere, Rigsby confesses his true feelings to Grace. Crime drama, starring Simon Baker, Owain Yeoman and Amanda Righetti.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: Bosco arrests Jane after discovering the bug in his office, leaving Cho and the other agents to investigate a murder case. They believe the victim was killed in a dispute over oil-rich land, and when they hand evidence over to Patrick he comes up with leads from the confines of his cell - before setting into motion an elaborate escape plan. Guest starring Ashley Jones (True Blood), with Simon Baker and Terry Kinney.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: Bosco and Lisbon reluctantly team up to investigate the kidnapping of a woman from a wealthy family. They suspect her abductors could have been behind a previous case in which a man was murdered, prompting Jane to take an unorthodox approach to save the victim's life before the ransom is paid. Crime drama, starring Terry Kinney, Robin Tunney and Simon Baker.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: Lisbon and the team are shocked to discover serial killer Red John targeted the CBI headquarters while they were out on assignment, leaving two agents dead and seriously wounding Bosco. Jane soon uncovers a link to another case, which leads him to vital evidence in the investigation - and the discovery that the criminal had an accomplice in the office. Crime drama, starring Robin Tunney and Simon Baker.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: Jane suspects an inside job when the team is called to a robbery at a jewellery store. After CCTV evidence confirms the involvement of a notorious safe-cracker, the agents discover he owed money to a professional criminal - but just when they think the case is closed, the business owner is taken hostage. Elsewhere, Van Pelt and Rigsby consider the future of their relationship. Crime drama, starring Simon Baker.(n)

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.desc: Peter is upset when his friends publicly make fun of him, so decides to find a more supportive social circle by befriending a group of women. However, Lois warns him that while his new friends may seem less harsh than the guys, they are probably talking about him behind his back.(n)

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.desc: Peter and Lois send Chris to space camp to boost his self-esteem. When his stint ends and the Griffins arrive to pick him up, they are accidentally launched into space and it is down to the awkward youth to land the clan safely back on Earth.(n)

programme.desc: Stan has his plans for Thanksgiving ruined when Francine's adoptive parents pay them an unexpected visit. Meanwhile, Francine's mother tries to get Hayley back into the dating world by setting her up with an eligible Chinese bachelor, who reveals his true intentions at the dinner table. Featuring the guest voice of Mariah Carey.(n)

programme.title: American Dad
programme.desc: Steve and his friends take a road trip to Snot's father's funeral, but the youngster's commitment to his mourning pal wavers when he falls in love along the way. Meanwhile, Stan and Roger create an automatic cake-cutting machine for the home shopping network - but disagree how to split the profits.(n)

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.desc: Peter loses his job as a forklift driver when he keeps pulling stunts at work, and it forces Lois to get an assistant manager job at a shop. Meanwhile, Quagmire and Joe try to provide advice when Lois admits she is tired of Peter's disappointing performances in the bedroom.(n)

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.desc: Three traditional fairy tales - Jack and the Beanstalk, Little Red Riding Hood and Cinderella - are given a Quahog spin on the original stories, with the Griffin family taking part in the adventures.(n)

programme.title: American Dad
programme.desc: Hayley decides she has had enough of being bossed around at home and moves in with her boyfriend. In an attempt to bring her back, Stan confiscates her credit card - so she finds a way to earn ready cash by becoming a stripper instead.(n)

programme.title: American Dad
programme.desc: Stan forgets his wedding anniversary and in desperation arranges to have 20 hours erased from Francine's memory at the CIA headquarters. However, the procedure goes awry and the hours are turned into years - so she reverts to her wild-child days and moves into her old apartment with Hayley.(n)

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.desc: Peter tries to build a multiplex to rival Joe's home theatre system, but disturbs an Indian burial ground by taking a skull from the site. Stewie is sucked into the TV and a series of spooky events follows as the restless spirits exact their revenge.(n)

programme.desc: Cleveland begins to socialise with Dr Fist, but a well-meaning attempt to get in touch with the medic's old friends reveals a potentially life-threatening secret. Meanwhile, Junior and Rallo open a mobile catering business at school, but their enterprise faces competition.(n)

programme.title: Family Guy
programme.desc: Part one of three. A brush with death scares Stewie into trying to be nice to the family, but his efforts fail miserably and he ends up becoming an alcoholic. Meanwhile, Peter lands a job on a TV news channel.(n)

programme.desc: Part two of three. Featuring the voices of Seth MacFarlane, Alex Borstein and Seth Green.(n)

programme.desc: The church deacon chokes on a communion wafer, prompting Stan to pull out all the stops in a bid to replace him. Meanwhile, Francine rustles up a potato salad for the wake using a secret ingredient provided by Roger, and Steve finds himself falling in love. With the voice of Josh Groban.(n)

programme.title: American Dad
programme.desc: Stan thinks his chances of promotion are over when Hayley disrupts the CIA family carnival. However, when he pays Director Bullock a home visit to apologise, he discovers his badly behaved daughter is the boss's new girlfriend.(n)

programme.desc: A girl takes desperate measures to avenge the years of abuse and neglect inflicted upon her by her psychotherapist parents. The events that follow culminate in tragedy for a man caught up in their promiscuity, mind games and competitiveness. Detective drama, starring Vincent D'Onofrio, Kathryn Erbe and Jamey Sheridan.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Returning from a six-month posting in the Gulf, Navy lieutenant commander Megan Huffner opens her front door to find her husband Noel dead in his chair. Gibbs and the team investigate and find the victim died three or four weeks earlier, and an unusual $100 bill in his wallet proves to be a vital clue. Meanwhile, Tony's father visits for Christmas and looks to rebuild their fractured relationship. Guest starring Robert Wagner.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Part one of two. A man and his son on a fishing trip hook what appears to be the body of a petty officer, but the dead man turns out to be a journalist who had been investigating the proliferation of drugs in the Navy. Meanwhile, Ziva returns to her car after a workout at the gym to find her father Eli hiding inside. Guest starring Michael Nouri.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Conclusion. After the deaths of two family members of NCIS employees, the team identifies the killer as a Swedish mercenary and the ballistics report reveals the bullets came from an Iranian arms dealer. McGee traces a wire transfer made to the hitman's ex-wife and son to an account under the name Virtue, and Ziva makes a connection after realising what the Hebrew translation is.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: The team is called to the scene of a fatal car crash involving marine lance corporal Chad Dunn and student Lyla Cutwright. Duckie notices that the woman's injuries do not match the specifics of the accident and there are no skidmarks found at the scene, leading Gibbs to declare they possibly have a murder and a suicide on their hands. Abby calls in sick for the first time after the case stirs up a traumatic incident from her childhood. Mark Harmon and Pauley Perrette star.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Gibbs and the team capture computer hacker Ajay Khan, who was recently responsible for hacking into NCIS's supposedly ultra-secure multiple-threat alert centre. They believe he could hold the key to tracking down the most-wanted cyber terrorist in the world, who may be plotting an attack using a bomb containing a strain of the Ebola virus. When Khan refuses to co-operate, Ziva and DiNozzo take him to Guantanamo Bay to be placed with people he had previously betrayed. Guest starring Vik Sahay (Chuck).(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: The murder of a trainer at a baseball academy leads Cho, Lisbon and Jane to suspect the crime could have been motivated by money. The team learns his wife is sole beneficiary of a substantial life insurance payout, and his business partner stood to take the controlling share of their company - but a lack of evidence hampers the investigation - until the consultant follows a hunch. Jane also has a flashback when he is knocked out, leading him to remember working at a circus with his father. Guest starring Jude Ciccolella.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: A couple are murdered on their way to a high-school reunion, prompting Patrick to investigate the untrustworthy characters at the event. He connects the incident to a past case of bullying, and when he notices that Rigsby bears a resemblance to one of the victims, he tries to lure the killer out with an audacious scheme. Crime drama, starring Simon Baker, Robin Tunney and Tim Kang.(n)

programme.desc: The corpse of a media-relations officer is unearthed at the opening of a new development in Salter, Central Valley. programme.desc: The body of a saleswoman is found in the boot of a car at a luxury showroom, and an autopsy reveals she was run over. programme.desc: Cho is forced to revisit old haunts and confront his murky past as he investigates the fatal shooting of a reformed criminal who used to belong to the same gang as him. programme.desc: Hugh Fearnley-Whittingstall joins Gill Mellow and Tim Maddams to resurrect a childhood favourite of crispy pancakes using smoked pollack, bacon, cheese and sweetcorn. He travels to Cornwall to meet fishermen who have found a sustainable and lucrative market in catching squid, and visits members of a community who are determined to grow and rear their own Christmas dinners. Hugh also draws inspiration from his garden as he prepares a chilli and pumpkin party for 200 people.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: The remaining six bakers have passed the halfway point of the contest, and now face three European bakes - beginning with yeast-leavened cakes, a tricky cross between cake and bread. Mary Berry then sets them the challenge of rustling up a Swedish princess torte, but they have their work cut out completing all 24 stages of the recipe in little more than two hours. They finish by creating their own version of the dobos torte, a multi-layered cake from Hungary. However, they must go one step further and bake a two-tiered version with an emphasis on caramel. Which of the bakers will come to a sticky end?.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Presenters Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins set the remaining contestants three tasks involving pastry, beginning by asking them to make signature savoury parcels. For the technical challenge, they must prepare a cake that hails from the Brittany region of France - the kouign amann, which none of the bakers has ever heard of - before creating two different types of eclair in the showstopper round. Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood judge the hopefuls' efforts before deciding who is star baker and who is going home.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: The nation's favourite baking contest has certainly proved it can hold its own after moving to BBC One - this series has been the most entertaining (not to mention contentious) yet. It's about to get a whole lot hotter in the kitchen, though, as it reaches the quarter-final stage, and just five amateur bakers remain. They've all impressed to various extents during Bread Week - at least sufficiently to make it through - but now their skills are thoroughly tested as they take on enriched doughs. They have a signature bake in which they must work with soft dough to create artful works, a technical that sees them recreate an Eastern European cross between bread and pastry, and a showstopper involving doughnuts.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Sue Perkins and Mel Giedroyc present as the remaining four bakers take a deep breath and head into the semi-final of the nation's favourite baking contest. However, there's no time to marvel at how far they've come - it's Patisserie Week, and they will need to demonstrate that they have skills worthy enough to see them through to this year's final. The bakers are challenged to make a signature baklava - two types of any flavour they like, before the technical challenge demands they knock up a German Schichttorte, a cake cooked in stages under the grill to create 20 layers of different coloured sponge. Finally, the showstopper sees the semi-finalists baking non-stop to create two entremets in which they should demonstrate as many personal skills and techniques as they can.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.sub-title: The Great British Bake Off: The Final.
programme.desc: Over the past 10 weeks, we have seen the amateur bakers whip up eclairs sprinkled with bacon, fire-breathing biscuit dragons and a very controversial baked Alaska. But now, just three contestants remain - and only one more weekend of baking stands between them and the trophy. Judges Paul Hollywood and Mary Berry have saved their most fiendish tests till last, as the finalists face a Signature Challenge in which they have just three hours to prove they have mastered a pastry technique that usually takes a whole day. They then have to tackle a Technical Challenge without the aid of a recipe, before rustling up a Showstopper that turns sponge, caramel, choux pastry and petits fours into a winning combination. At least Sue Perkins and Mel Giedroyc are on hand to lighten the atmosphere if it all gets too tense.(n)

programme.title: Coraline
programme.desc: Director Henry Selick (The Nightmare Before Christmas; James and the Giant Peach) delivers a deliciously dark stop-motion animated adventure for children who don't mind a scare or two, based on Neil Gaiman's much-praised book. Coraline Jones and her parents have just moved into the Pink Palaces Apartments in Oregon, where they find themselves surrounded by eccentric neighbours, including a pair of ageing burlesque performers. It should be an exciting time, but Coraline's parents are too busy working as horticultural journalists to spend any time with her, so she is deeply bored. That is until she discovers a mysterious door that only appears after dark. Bold and inquisitive, the youngster investigates. She discovers a brightly coloured alternative universe, where her 'Other Mother' has plenty of time to play with her and her neighbours' quirks are charmingly exaggerated; in fact, she's tempted to stay. But all is not as it seems: everyone in the new world has buttons for eyes - and the operation to install them involves knitting needles. And that revelation is just the first of her shocking discoveries about the true nature of her apparent idyll... So, there's definitely good reason for that PG certificate, though children who can cope with the story of Hansel and Gretel shouldn't find anything too disturbing here. Selick's film won great critical acclaim, and scooped festival prizes around the world, as well as picking up an Oscar nomination and winning the 2009 BAFTA Children's Award. Also featuring the voices of Keith David, Robert Bailey Jr and Ian McShane(n)

programme.title: Madagascar: Escape 2 Africa
programme.desc: Hopelessly stranded on the remote shores of Madagascar, the New Yorkers hatch a plan to get back to Central Park that instead finds them soaking up sun in the picturesque plains of Africa. Madagascar may be a nice place to visit, but for the gang of animals who spent most of their lives in New York, there is truly no place like home. After discovering the remnants of a crashed airplane, the penguins quickly set about making the repairs needed to get the craft airborne again. When the plane finally takes to the sky, it begins to look like it's only a matter of time before Alex the Lion (voice of Ben Stiller) and friends are soaring over New York Harbor. Unfortunately the penguins weren't the aviation experts they claimed to be, and before long the crew is coming in for a crash-landing in the untamed plains of Africa. Now, as the animals reared in the safety of the zoo come into contact with their decidedly wild counterparts for the very first time, they get a better feel for their roots while marveling over the differences between life in the concrete jungle and life on the world's second largest continent. Of course, while there's plenty to love about wandering the open plains, romantic rivalries and the risk of running into dangerous poachers soon begin to outweigh the joys of some long-overdue family reunions. With some particularly heavy cases of homesickness causing hearts to weigh heavy, the group gradually starts to wonder whether they'll ever find their way back home. Chris Rock, David Schwimmer, Jada Pinkett Smith, Sacha Baron Cohen, Cedric the Entertainer, and Andy Richter lend their voices to this animated sequel that re-teams original Madagascar co-directors Eric Darnell and Tom McGrath(n)

programme.title: Trail of the Pink Panther
programme.desc: An intrepid reporter investigates the mysterious disappearance of the bumbling Inspector Clouseau. Comedy sequel made after star Peter Sellers' death, using out-takes and unused footage from previous Pink Panther films, with Joanna Lumley, David Niven, Herbert Lom and Burt Kwouk.(n)

programme.title: Alien Autopsy
programme.desc: Video dealer Ray and his friend Gary stumble onto what seems to be footage of an alien autopsy and plan to sell it. But when the film is destroyed, they resort to re-creating the incident in their kitchen. Comedy, based on the infamous 1995 hoax, starring Anthony McPartlin, Declan Donnelly, Omid Djalili, Bill Pullman and Harry Dean Stanton.(n)

programme.title: Mr Woodcock
programme.desc: The successful author of a self-help book has managed to put the painful memories of being bullied by his PE teacher as a chubby youngster behind him. However, when he returns to his home town to accept a prestigious award, the writer is horrified to discover his mother is planning to marry his childhood tormentor. Comedy, starring Billy Bob Thornton, Seann William Scott and Susan Sarandon.(n)

programme.title: The Heartbreak Kid
programme.desc: A 40-year-old bachelor decides he has been far too picky in his love life, so he hastily proposes to his girlfriend of several weeks. The future looks rosy as they jet off on their honeymoon, but when he discovers an unpleasant side to his new wife's personality he is tempted to look elsewhere for romance. The Farrelly brothers' comedy, starring Ben Stiller, Michelle Monaghan and Malin Akerman.(n)

programme.title: Wedding Crashers
programme.desc: Two party-mad bachelors make the most of the romantic atmosphere as they gatecrash weddings to pick up women. With a catalogue of tall stories to tell guests, the pair are regularly the hit of the events they attend - until one of them falls for a bridesmaid and they both learn a few things about love. Comedy, starring Owen Wilson, Vince Vaughn, Christopher Walken, Jane Seymour, Rachel McAdams and Isla Fisher.(n)

programme.title: Spy - Extended Version
programme.desc: A deskbound CIA agent provides valuable background support for a dashing secret agent, but has never gone into action herself. Everything changes, when the spy mysteriously vanishes, and she leaps into action to take his place, infiltrating the inner circle of a ruthless arms dealer and trying to avert a global catastrophe. Comedy adventure, starring Melissa McCarthy, Jason Statham and Rose Byrne.(n)

programme.title: I Spy
programme.desc: A hapless spy is assigned to track down an underground arms dealer who has stolen a prototype jet fighter. His superiors decide the best way for him to get close to his target is to pose as an assistant to an egotistical boxing champion, who revels at the chance to become a secret agent. Spy comedy based on the 1960s TV series, starring Eddie Murphy, Owen Wilson, Famke Janssen and Malcolm McDowell.(n)

programme.title: Dumb and Dumber To
programme.desc: Dim-witted friends Harry and Lloyd are reunited after 20 years. When Harry discovers he has a daughter he never knew about, he breaks his friend out of a psychiatric hospital and they go on a road trip with the intention of fulfilling parental responsibilities neither of them is capable of. Comedy sequel, starring Jim Carrey and Jeff Daniels.(n)

programme.desc: Bumbling scientist Sherman Klump is engaged to be married and determined to rid himself of his troublesome alter ego Buddy Love for ever. All his problems look set to be solved by his fiancee's latest DNA experiment - but things are about to spiral out of control. Comedy sequel, starring Eddie Murphy in multiple roles, along with Janet Jackson and Larry Miller.(n)

programme.title: Tenacious D in The Pick of Destiny
programme.desc: A would-be rock star flees his repressive Christian father in search of stardom, teaming up with a laid-back guitarist along the way. However, for the duo to become the rock gods they are surely destined to be, they must find a magical guitar pick that gives its owner unprecedented musical prowess - a quest that leads them to a confrontation with Satan himself. Comedy, starring Jack Black, Kyle Gass, Meat Loaf, Dave Grohl, Tim Robbins, Ben Stiller and John C Reilly.(n)

programme.title: The Curse of the Pink Panther
programme.desc: Inspector Clouseau vanishes without trace and another detective must be chosen to solve the mystery of his disappearance. Glad to be rid of the bane of his existence, Clouseau's long-suffering boss makes sure an even more inept investigator gets the job. Comedy, starring Herbert Lom, Ted Wass, Joanna Lumley, David Niven and Robert Wagner.(n)

programme.title: (GMT) Twins (1988)
programme.desc: An unlikely pair of brothers, who were born as the result of a one-off genetic experiment and separated at birth, are reunited in adulthood. They set out on a cross-country search for their unknown mother - fending off vicious loan sharks and a professional assassin along the way. Comedy, starring Arnold Schwarzenegger, Danny DeVito, Kelly Preston and Chloe Webb.(n)

programme.title: Valentine's Day
programme.desc: Anthology of stories charting the romantic complications of various Los Angeles residents. A businessman and a soldier on leave share a flight home, a teacher is smitten with a doctor and an elderly couple comfort their lovesick grandson. Romantic comedy drama, with Ashton Kutcher, Jessica Alba, Jamie Foxx, Jennifer Garner and Julia Roberts.(n)

programme.title: The Top Ten Show 2016

programme.title: Rushmore
programme.desc: A student causes chaos in an exclusive private school with his temperamental nature - and things go from bad to worse when he develops a crush on a teacher. A wealthy but miserable businessman strikes up a friendship with the troubled teenager, but when he also falls for the same woman, all-out war is declared. Wes Anderson's comedy drama, starring Jason Schwartzman, Bill Murray, Olivia Williams and Brian Cox.(n)

programme.title: Sister Act
programme.desc: Nightclub singer Deloris Van Cartier agrees to testify against her gangster boyfriend after witnessing a murder. Placed in protective custody by the authorities, she is less than pleased to discover she is expected to pose as chaste nun Sister Mary Clarence in a convent. Comedy, starring Whoopi Goldberg, Harvey Keitel, Maggie Smith, Bill Nunn and Kathy Najimy.(n)

programme.desc: The foul-mouthed talking teddy bear is horrified to discover that he counts as property according to the law. He and his human best friend hire a pot-smoking lawyer to help them fight a court case and get Ted legally recognised as a person. Comedy sequel, starring Mark Wahlberg and Amanda Seyfried, with the voice of Seth MacFarlane.(n)

programme.desc: The sex-mad spy is sent back to swinging London at the height of the 1960s in pursuit of the dastardly Dr Evil, who has stolen the secret agent's `mojo'. Teaming up with a female American agent, Austin must stop his arch-rival from causing havoc with a doomsday weapon on the moon. Comedy sequel, starring Mike Myers in multiple roles alongside Heather Graham, Rob Lowe, Robert Wagner, Michael York, Seth Green and Verne Troyer.(n)
